Name: vads-color-aqua
description: Use of this sass variable will move to vads-color-primary-alt and then be retired.

Name: vads-color-aqua-dark
description: Use of this sass variable will move to vads-color-primary-alt-dark and then be retired.

Name: vads-color-aqua-lightest
description: This will move to vads-color-primary-alt-lightest and then be retired.

Name: vads-color-blue
description: This is identical to vads-color-primary and instances should be converted and removed.

Name: vads-color-blue-darkest
description: Identical to vads-color-primary-darkest and should be converted and removed.

Name: vads-color-blue-light
description: This is identical to vads-color-primary and instances should be converted and removed.

Name: vads-color-orange
description: This will likely be replaced by semantic tokens in future.

Name: vads-color-purple
description: Identical to vads-color-link-visited and thus will be removed.

Name: vads-color-red
description: Identical to vads-color-secondary and instances should be converted and removed.

Name: vads-color-red-dark
description: Identical to vads-color-secondary-dark and any instances should be converted and removed.

Name: vads-color-red-light
description: Identical to vads-color-secondary-light and any instances (I couldn't find any)  should be converted and removed.

Name: vads-color-red-lightest
description: Identical to vads-color-secondary-lightest and instances should be converted and removed.
